<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Antidactylaria minifimbriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Z.F. Yu, M. Qiao &amp; R.F. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Castañeda">Castaneda</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. F. Yu, M. Qiao &amp; R. F. Castaneda" authorityYear="2021" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="Antidactylaria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Antidactylaria" order="Microthyriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Antidactylaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is superficially similar to the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Leotiomycetes" family="Calloriaceae" genus="Dactylaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dactylaria" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Dactylaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sacc. in morphology. The genus 
<taxonomicName class="Leotiomycetes" family="Calloriaceae" genus="Dactylaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dactylaria" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Dactylaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, typified with 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. purpurella" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="purpurella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. purpurella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Sacc.) Sacc., is characterised by unbranched, septate, hyaline or pigmented conidiophores, denticulate, integrated, mostly terminal, sympodially extending conidiogenous cells and cylindrical, fusiform, filiform, ellipsoid, clavate, obclavate, unicellular or septate, hyaline or pale pigmented conidia that are liberated with schizolytic secession (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0953756297004000" author="Goh, TK" journalOrPublisher="Mycological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1265 - 1272" refId="B14" refString="Goh, TK, Hyde, KD, 1997. A revision of Dactylaria, with description of D. tunicata sp. nov. from submerged wood in Australia. Mycological Research 101 (10): 1265 - 1272, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1017/S0953756297004000" title="A revision of Dactylaria, with description of D. tunicata sp. nov. from submerged wood in Australia." url="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0953756297004000" volume="101" year="1997">Goh and Hyde 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/yea.955" author="Paulus, B" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="143 - 156" refId="B33" refString="Paulus, B, Gadek, P, Hyde, KD, 2003. Two new species of Dactylaria (anamorphic fungi) from Australian rainforests and an update of species in Dactylaria sensu lato. Fungal Diversity 14: 143 - 156, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/yea.955" title="Two new species of Dactylaria (anamorphic fungi) from Australian rainforests and an update of species in Dactylaria sensu lato." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/yea.955" volume="14" year="2003">Paulus et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Seifert, K" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B49" refString="Seifert, K, Morgan-Jones, G, Gams, W, Kendrick, B, 2011. The genera of hyphomycetes. CBS Biodiversity Series 9: 997." title="The genera of hyphomycetes. CBS Biodiversity Series 9: 997." year="2011">Seifert et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). However, the rhexolytic conidial secession, observed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. F. Yu, M. Qiao &amp; R. F. Castaneda" authorityYear="2021" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="Antidactylaria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Antidactylaria" order="Microthyriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Antidactylaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is absent in 
<taxonomicName class="Leotiomycetes" family="Calloriaceae" genus="Dactylaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dactylaria" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Dactylaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/yea.955" author="Paulus, B" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="143 - 156" refId="B33" refString="Paulus, B, Gadek, P, Hyde, KD, 2003. Two new species of Dactylaria (anamorphic fungi) from Australian rainforests and an update of species in Dactylaria sensu lato. Fungal Diversity 14: 143 - 156, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/yea.955" title="Two new species of Dactylaria (anamorphic fungi) from Australian rainforests and an update of species in Dactylaria sensu lato." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/yea.955" volume="14" year="2003">Paulus et al. (2003)</bibRefCitation>
discussed the conidiogenous event as an important criterion for generic delimitation. In addition, phylogeny analysis showed that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. F. Yu, M. Qiao &amp; R. F. Castaneda" authorityYear="2021" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="Antidactylaria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Antidactylaria" order="Microthyriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Antidactylaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. F. Yu, M. Qiao &amp; R. F. Castaneda" authorityYear="2021" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="Antidactylaria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Microthyriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="order">Microthyriales</taxonomicName>
, while 
<taxonomicName class="Leotiomycetes" family="Calloriaceae" genus="Dactylaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dactylaria" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Dactylaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species belong to 
<taxonomicName class="Leotiomycetes" genus="Dactylaria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="order">Helotiales</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
